text: Quilby Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Alabama. Quilby is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "creek where the panther was killed". Variant names are "Koilbah Creek", "Quibby Creek", and "Quillibee Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Sumter County, Alabama
title: Quilby Creek
